The <span class="text-green font-bold">All India Khilafat Committee</span> was primarily established in <span class="text-magenta font-bold">1919</span> by the "<span class="text-blue font-bold">Ali Brothers</span>"—<span class="text-orange font-bold"></span><span class="text-orange" style="font-weight: 800;">Maulana Mohammad Ali Jauhar and Maulana Shaukat Ali</span> - to protest against the British dismantling of the Ottoman Caliphate post-WWI. As <span class="text-green" style="font-weight: 800;">Arabs rebelled Ottomans</span>, guided by <span class="text-teal" style="font-weight: 800;">British officer Lawrence of Arabia</span>, it Split the Ottoman empire restricting it to modern day Turkey. This later led the<span class="text-magenta" style="font-weight: 800;"> Sykes-Picot Agreement</span> dividing Ottoman lands to various Arab states, giving part of it to<span class="text-blue" style="font-weight: 800;"> create Israel</span>. The movement merged with <span class="text-orange" style="font-weight: 800;">Gandhi’s Non-Cooperation Movement, </span>triggering a major<span class="text-teal" style="font-weight: 800;"> joint Hindu-Muslim revolt </span>against British rule in 1920–22 and calling for <span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">restoring of Ottoman empire</span>. It collapsed in 1924 when Atatürk abolished the Caliphate completely<span style="font-style: italic;"> ending the last powerful remnant of powerful Muslim empire</span>.<div><div> <div class="nk-video-wrapper" data-video-url="https://youtube.com/shorts/2QFlOr-Dav4?si=n0en0vqbjMKSxaoB" data-video-platform="youtube" data-video-aspect="9/16" data-align="center" style="width:100%; max-width:340px; aspect-ratio:9/16;
